<section id="research" class="post mt-5 pt-4" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--global-divider-color);">
  <h2><a href="{{ '/research/' | relative_url }}" style="color: inherit">research</a></h2>

  <p>
    My primary research investigates the dynamic behaviour of large-scale hyperbolic cooling towers under seismic and wind loading,
    with a focus on the Rooppur Nuclear Power Plant in Bangladesh — the country's first nuclear power plant, located near the
    seismically active Madhupur Fault.
  </p>

  <p>
    Using <strong>ABAQUS</strong>, I developed detailed finite element models of the 175 m cooling tower and compared two column
    modelling strategies: an <strong>Embedded Reinforcement</strong> approach and a <strong>Simplified Timoshenko Beam</strong> approach.
    Both models were subjected to the 2001 Bhuj/Kachchh earthquake and wind loads calculated via Greiner's equation per BNBC-2020.
  </p>

  <div class="row mt-3 mb-2 justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-sm-8">
